CLINICAL GUIDELINE: HYPERTENSION MANAGEMENT
Version 1.0 | Published: Jan 2026 | HCL Tech Medical Guidelines

1. DEFINITIONS
Stage 1 Hypertension: Systolic 130-139 mmHg OR Diastolic 80-89 mmHg

2. FIRST-LINE MANAGEMENT
2.1 Non-pharmacological
- Lifestyle modification (Diet, Exercise, Weight loss)
- Target: 5-10% weight reduction in 6 months

2.2 Pharmacological (if lifestyle fails after 3 months)
- Start with single agent: Thiazide diuretic OR ACE inhibitor
- Preferred: Chlorthalidone 12.5mg daily
- Alternative: Lisinopril 10mg daily

3. MONITORING
- Check BP every 4 weeks
- Monitor potassium if on ACE inhibitors
- Annual renal function test

4. CONTRAINDICATIONS
- Thiazides: G6PD deficiency, severe renal impairment
- ACE inhibitors: Pregnancy, bilateral renal artery stenosis

5. REFERRAL CRITERIA
- Resistant hypertension (3 drugs)
- Secondary hypertension suspicion
- BP >180/110 mmHg

END OF GUIDELINE
Source: HCL Tech Internal Guidelines 2026